Program: Thinking Allowed
Title: Shyness - Names
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b07w94h5
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 26 Sep 2016
Shyness: Laurie Taylor talks to Joe Moran, Professor of English and Cultural History at Liverpool John Moores University and the author of study of the 'shrinking violet' in history and sociology. Also, a sociology of naming. Jane Pilcher, Associate Professor of Sociology at the University of Leicester, explores the relationship between names and our sense of identity. Producer: Jayne Egerton. Show less